events.name: New Mexico State Aggies at Liberty Flames

headlines.description: — Kaidon Salter threw for two touchdowns and ran for another, and undefeated No. 20 Liberty maintained its hopes of a New Year's Six bowl bid, beating New Mexico State 49-35 in the Conference USA championship game on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kaidon Salter leads unbeaten No. 20 Liberty past New Mexico State 49-35 for C-USA title

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: — Michigan coach Jim Harbaugh celebrated his return to the sideline Saturday by hugging players and evasively running to avoid a Gatorade bath.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 2 Michigan beats No. 18 Iowa 26-0 for Big Ten title, likely to claim top playoff seed

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: — Florida State coach Mike Norvell said the possibility of leaving his unbeaten Seminoles out of the College Football Playoff shouldn't even be discussed.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 4 Florida State beats No. 15 Louisville 16-6 for ACC title, but could miss playoff at 13-0

video.headline: Braden Fiske's huge sack helps FSU seal ACC title

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: — Quinn Ewers and the Texas Longhorns are leaving the Big 12 with bookend championships and still hoping for a chance at the College Football Playoff. As for their fans, it was good riddance to the commissioner they felt was rooting against them.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ewers throws 4 TDs as No. 7 Texas bids farewell to Big 12 with 49-21 title win over Oklahoma State

video.headline: Quinn Ewers shines with 4 first-half TDs in Big 12 title game

events.name: SMU Mustangs at Tulane Green Wave

headlines.description: — SMU quarterback Kevin Jennings got hit in his throwing arm and fumbled on the first play of his first career start in a conference championship game on the road.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jennings, dominant defense carry No. 25 SMU to AAC title, 26-14 over Tulane

events.name: Boise State Broncos at UNLV Rebels

headlines.description: — A locker room can go either way when a coaching change is made, and in Boise State's case, players lined up behind Spencer Danielson when he was handed the job on an interim basis with two games left in the regular season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green, Jeanty lead Boise State to 44-20 win over UNLV for Mountain West title
